17 (2) Plumbing and properly functioning sanitary facilities;
18 (3) Availability of hot and cold water;
19 (4) Appliances that are properly installed and in safe working condition;
20 (5) No evidence of mold;
21 (6) Operable fire, smoke, and carbon monoxide detectors; and
22 (7) Buildings, grounds, and common areas that are maintained as clean, sanitary, and free
23 from debris, garbage, rodents, insects, and vermin.
24 (b) The landlord shall keep the premises in repair and shall be liable for all substantial
25 improvements placed upon the premises by such landlord's consent.
26 (b)(c) Any contract, lease, license, or similar agreement, oral or written, for the use or
27 rental of real property as a dwelling place is deemed to include a provision that the
28 premises is fit for human habitation."
29 SECTION 2.
30 Said article is further amended by revising subsection (a) of Code Section 44-7-14.1, relating
31 to landlord's duties as to utilities, as follows:
32 "(a) As used in this Code section, the term 'utilities' means cooling, heat, light, and hot and
33 cold water service."
34 SECTION 3.
35 Said article is further amended by adding new Code sections to read as follows:
36 "44-7-25.
37 (a) A landlord shall not require that a prospective tenant be required to earn at or above
38 three times the monthly allotted rent when the prospective tenant is using any type of
39 government voucher to subsidize their rent. This includes but is not limited to:
40 (1) Housing Choice Vouchers;
41 (2) Tenant Protection Vouchers;
