125 44-7-26.
126 (a) It shall be unlawful for a person to:
127 (1) Refuse to sell or rent a dwelling after a bona fide offer has been made, or to refuse
128 to negotiate for the sale or rental of a dwelling, because of race, color, religion, sex,
129 familial status, source of income, or national origin, or to discriminate in the sale or rental
130 of a dwelling because of disability;
131 (2) Discriminate in the terms, conditions, or privileges of sale or rental of a dwelling, or
132 in the provision of services or facilities in connection with such sale or rental, because of
133 race, color, religion, sex, disability, familial status, source of income, or national origin;
134 (3) Engage in any conduct relating to the provision of housing which otherwise makes
135 unavailable or denies dwellings to persons because of race, color, religion, sex, disability,
136 familial status, source of income, or national origin;
137 (4) Make, print, or publish, or cause to be made, printed, or published, any notice,
138 statement, or advertisement with respect to the sale or rental of a dwelling that indicates
139 any preference, limitation, or discrimination because of race, color, religion, sex,
140 disability, source of income, familial status, or national origin, or any intention to make
141 any such preference, limitation, or discrimination;
142 (5) Represent to any person because of race, color, religion, sex, disability, familial
143 status, source of income, or national origin that a dwelling is not available for sale or
144 rental when such dwelling is in fact available;
